7 An Act relating to milk; amending 2 O.S. 2021,
Section 7-414, which relates to the Oklahoma Milk and
8 Milk Products Act; modifying construing provision to
allow for the sale and advertising of certain milk
9 products at specific locations; removing gallon limit
for incidental sale of goat milk; and providing an
10 effective date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 2 O.S. 2021, Section 7-414, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 7-414. A. The provisions of the Oklahoma Milk and Milk
17 Products Act shall not be construed to:
18 1. Include incidental sales of raw, unpasteurized cow milk,
19 goat milk, or sheep milk directly to consumers at:
20 a. at the farm where the milk is produced,
21 b. at feed stores; however, the container the milk is
22 being sold out of must be conspicuously labeled with
23 signage stating "Unpasteurized Milk",
24
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3056 Page 1

1 c. at a farmer's market; however, the container the milk
2 is being sold out of must be conspicuously labeled
3 with signage stating "Unpasteurized Milk", or
4 d. via delivery from the farm where the milk is produced;
5 2. Preclude Prohibit the advertising of the incidental sale of
6 raw, unpasteurized cow milk, goat milk, or sheep milk; and or
7 3. Prohibit any farmer or producer from making cheese using
8 milk or cream produced on the farm of such farmer or producer.
9 B. For purposes of this section, incidental sales of goat milk
10 are those sales where the average monthly number of gallons sold
11 does not exceed one hundred (100).
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
13 Passed the House of Representatives the 24th day of March, 2026.
